# CommonJS ðŸ“¦

Node used `require()` for years (CommonJS).

```javascript
// math.js
module.exports = { add: (a,b) => a+b };

// app.js
const math = require('./math');
console.log(math.add(1, 2));
```
Modern Node also supports ES Modules (`import/export`) if configured.

# Raw HTTP ðŸŒ

```javascript
const http = require('http');

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.statusCode = 200;
  res.end('Hello World');
});

server.listen(3000);
```
Most people use frameworks like **Express** instead of raw `http`.

